## Git and PR conventions

- **Never commit directly to `main`** вЂ” always work on a feature branch
- Keep `main` current: `git fetch upstream && git merge --ff-only upstream/main`
- Commit style: conventional commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `test:`)
- Open PRs with `gh pr create` вЂ” target branch: `main` on `${FORK_REPO_PATH}`
- **Never merge your own PRs** вЂ” user approval is required at every gate

